{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Refimprove|date=August 2013}} {{Infobox architectural practice | name = LMN | logo = LMN Architects logo.svg | logo_size = 150px | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | caption = | architects = | partners = | founders = | employees = | city = [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], [[United States]] | coordinates = {{coords|47.603733|-122.334540|region:US-WA|display=inline,title}} | affiliations = | founded = 1979 | awards = 2016 Architecture Firm Award from [[American Institute of Architects]]<ref>{{cite press release |date=December 3, 2015 |title=LMN Architects Receive the 2016 AIA Architecture Firm Award |url=http://www.aia.org/press/releases/AIAB107713 |publisher=[[American Institute of Architects]] |accessdate=March 5, 2016}}</ref> | significant_buildings = [[4/C]], [[808 Howell Street]], [[Expedia Building]] | significant_projects = | significant_design = | website = {{URL|http://lmnarchitects.com/|lmnarchitects.com}} }}
'''LMN''' is an American [[architecture firm]] based in [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]]. The company was founded in 1979, and provides planning and design services to create convention centers, cultural arts venues, higher education facilities, commercial and mixed-use developments.
==Features== LMN has been published in "On the Right Track" in ''[[The Architect's Newspaper]]'',<ref>{{cite web|author=Sam Lubell and Ariel Rosenstock |url=http://archpaper.com/news/articles.asp?id=6182 |title=On The Right Track - The Architect's Newspaper |publisher=Archpaper.com |date=July 25, 2012 |accessdate=August 19, 2013}}</ref> as well as in "Vancouver Convention Centre Pushes Limit on Green Design," from Contract Design Magazine,<ref>{{citation|author=Stacy Straczynski |url=http://www.contractdesign.com/contract/ls/Archived-Article-1403.shtml?articletitle=DESIGN-DESIGN%20NEWS_Vancouver%20Convention%20Centre%20Pushes%20Limit%20on%20Green%20Design_214.xml| |title=Vancouver Convention Centre Pushes Limit on Green Design |publisher=Contractdesign.com | date=May 10, 2010}}</ref> "Advancing Data-Driven Approach to Architecture" in the Metropolis Magazine,<ref>{{cite web|author=Sam Miller |url=http://www.metropolismag.com/Point-of-View/April-2012/Advancing-a-Data-Driven-Approach-to-Architecture/index.php?tagID=562 |title=Advancing a Data-Driven Approach to Architecture - Point of View - April 2012 |publisher=Metropolismag.com |date=April 10, 2012}}</ref> and the ''[[Seattle Times]]'' its contribution to the Seattle Public Library.<ref>{{cite web|author=Susan Gilmore |url=http://seattletimes.com/html/localnews/2001930967_lmn17m.html |title=Seattle's LMN architects part of library team |publisher=The Seattle Times |date=May 17, 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spl.org/locations/central-library/cen-building-facts |title=CEN Building Facts &#124; The Seattle Public Library |publisher=Spl.org |date=May 23, 2004}}</ref>
==Awards== The firm has received over 100 awards in the past 10 years. Most recently, LMN's work on the Vancouver Convention Centre West was awarded Sustainable Building of the Year from World Architecture News.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldarchitecturenews.com/index.php?fuseaction=wanappln.projectview&upload_id=21893 |title=WAN Sustainable Building of the Year Winner, LMN Architects, world architecture news, architecture jobs |publisher=Worldarchitecturenews.com |date=February 18, 2013}}</ref> The firm was also awarded 2012 Regional Firm of the Year by the American Institute of Architects (AIA) Northwest & Pacific Region<ref>[http://www.aianwpr.org/2012/10/23/2012-region-firm-award/ AIA Northwest & Pacific Region Names LMN Architecture Inaugural 2012 Region Firm Award Winner], AIA Northwest & Pacific Region</ref> as well as Chicago Athenaeum American Architecture award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chi-athenaeum.org/archawards/2012/AA12-103/index.html |title=2012 American Architecture Awards |publisher=Chi-athenaeum.org |date=October 23, 2012}}</ref> A few other awards the firm has earned are: * AIA National Cote Award for the Vancouver Convention Centre West * Sustainable Architecture & Building Magazine Award of Sustainability * Excellence in Construction Award for the Salem Conference Center * International Illumination Design Award, Award of Merit for the Marion Oliver McCaw Hall * Lumen West Award of Excellence for the Marion Oliver McCaw Hall
